BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (18): TURKEY (KUTAHYA) OVINE, SEROTYPE 4, OIE
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 24 Nov 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2015; 28(48) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=19167


Bluetongue, Turkey
--------------------
Information received on [and dated] 24 Nov 2015 from Prof. Dr Irfan Erol, Director General of Food and Control, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock, Ankara, Turkey

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 6 Oct 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 20 Nov 2015
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 15 Dec 2014
Manifestation of disease: sub- clinical infection
Causal agent: bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Kurtcam, Kutahya
Date of start of the outbreak: 6 Oct 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 833 / 7 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 0.84 / 0 / 0 / 0
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors
Epidemiological comments: The virus was confirmed on 20 Nov 2015 as bluetongue virus serotype 4 by the reports of Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute, which is the national reference laboratory for bluetongue.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestation; quarantine; control of vectors; no treatment of affected animals; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated
Kutahya / Sheep / 5600
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute (national laboratory) / Sheep / real-time reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 20 Nov 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In 2014, Turkey reported to the OIE 4 outbreaks of bluetongue serotype 4 in sheep. These outbreaks were located in the provinces of Kirklareli, Balikesir, and Canakkale. In response to the outbreaks, 450 774 sheep were vaccinated. See annual report 2014 at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/semestrial/review?year=2014&semester=0&wild=0&country=TUR&this_country_code=TUR&detailed=1.

For a general overview of the BTV situation in the area, please see the bluetongue outbreak map provided by the OIE's WAHID database for the time frame 1 Jan 2014 to 24 Nov 2015 at http://tinyurl.com/jnheml5. Click on the territory of choice, and zoom in. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3816436,87.]
